          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>paneer</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped paneer </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated paneer</strong> to the pan with your <strong>cashews</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
